Weyl (chiral) basis
Another common choice is the Weyl or chiral basis, in which 
  
    
      
        
          γ
          
            k
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \gamma ^{k}}
   remains the same but 
  
    
      
        
          γ
          
            0
          
        
      
    
